John Brennan, Assistant to the President for Homeland Security and Counterterrorism, spoke with Yemeni Vice President Abdo Rabbo Mansour al-Hadi to commend him for announcing early presidential elections on February 21, 2012. They discussed the importance of implementing the terms of the November 23 political settlement and working together to fulfill the aspirations of the Yemeni people. Brennan emphasized the need for all parties to refrain from violence and proceed with the transition peacefully. He also reiterated the commitment of the United States to support Yemen's government and people as they pursue a more secure, prosperous, and democratic future.